0.1 Basic Box Plot

  • library(ggplot2): To load ggplot the function to process on R Script

  • ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight)) Use PlantGrowth dataset and set group on the x-axis, and weight on the y-axis.

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(title = 'Basic Box Plot',
       caption = 'Valencia, DV, THU 2024') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

0.2 Add Legends

  • library(gridExtra): To load the gridextra to use the grid.arrange function
  • fill: To add colors inside the charts
  • color: To add color of the outline of the charts
  • grid.arrange: To arrange the boxplots
  • top: To add title on the top of the plot
  • bottom: To add captions at the bottom of the plot
library(gridExtra)
p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight)) + 
  geom_boxplot()
p2 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, 
                              y = weight, 
                              fill = group)) + 
  geom_boxplot()
p3 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, 
                              y = weight,
                              color = group)) + 
  geom_boxplot()

grid.arrange(p1,p2,p3,ncol=3,
             top='Add Legend', 
             bottom = 'Valencia, DV, THU 2024')

1 Remove Legend

  • guides(fill = FALSE) is to remove the Legend
ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) + 
  geom_boxplot() +
  guides(fill = FALSE) +
  ggtitle('Remove Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))
Warning: The `<scale>` argument of `guides()` cannot be `FALSE`. Use "none" instead as
of ggplot2 3.3.4.

2 Change Color of Legend

  • scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") is to change the color/theme of the Legend
ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") +
  ggtitle('Change Color of Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

3 Change Position of Legend

  • legend.position = 'top' is to change the position of the legend to the top
ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") +
  ggtitle('Change Color of Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5),
        legend.position = 'top')

4 Practice

  • p2 <- p1 + theme(legend.position = 'bottom') is to change legend position to top, bottom, left, and right
p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") +
  ggtitle('Change Color of Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5),
        legend.position = 'top')
p2 <- p1 + theme(legend.position = 'bottom')
p3 <- p1 + theme(legend.position = 'left')
p4 <- p1 + theme(legend.position = 'right')

grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, p4, ncol=2,
             top='Chainging Position of Legend')

6 Change Border of Legend

ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") +
  ggtitle('Change Border of Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5),
        legend.position = c(0.85, 0.2),
        legend.background = element_rect(fill = 'white',
                                         color = 'black'))

7 Change Background of Legend

ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") +
  ggtitle('Change Background of Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5),
        legend.position = c(0.85, 0.2),
        legend.background = element_blank(),
        legend.key = element_blank())

8 Change Order of Items in Legend

p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ggtitle('Change Order of Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

p2 <- p1 + scale_fill_discrete(limits = c('trt1', 'trt2', 'crtl'))

grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2)

9 Reverse Order of Items in Legend

p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ggtitle('Reversing Order of Items') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

p2 <- p1 + guides(fill = guide_legend(reverse = TRUE))

grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2)

10 Change Legend Title

p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ggtitle('Changing Legend Title') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

p2 <- p1 + labs(fill = 'Condition')

grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2)

11 Change Appearance of Legend Title

p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ggtitle('Changing Legend Title') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

p2 <- p1 + theme(legend.title = element_text(face = 'italic',
                                             family = 'Times',
                                             color = 'red',
                                             size = 14))
grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2)

12 Remove Legend Title

p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ggtitle('Removing Legend Title') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

p2 <- p1 + guides(fill = guide_legend(title = NULL))

grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2)

13 Change Labels in Legend

p1 <- ggplot(PlantGrowth, aes(x = group, y = weight, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ggtitle('Change Labels in Legend') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

p2 <- p1 + 
  scale_fill_discrete(labels = c('Control',
                                 'Treatment 1',
                                 'Treatment 2'))

grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2)

15 Legend with Multiple Variables

library(gcookbook)
ggplot(heightweight, aes(x = ageYear, y = heightIn, colour = sex)) +
  geom_point(aes(size = weightLb)) +
  scale_size_continuous(range = c(1, 4)) +
  ggtitle('Legend with Multiple Variables')

16 Resize the Point

library(gcookbook)
ggplot(heightweight, aes(x = ageYear, y = heightIn, colour = sex)) +
  geom_point(aes(size = weightLb)) +
  labs(colour = "Male/Female", size = "Weight\n(pounds)") +
  ggtitle('Legend with Multiple Variables')

18 Change Labels in Legend

library(gcookbook)
ggplot(heightweight, aes(x = ageYear, y = heightIn, colour = sex)) +
  geom_point(aes(size = weightLb)) +
  scale_size_continuous(range = c(1, 4)) +
  labs(colour = "Male/Female", size = "Weight\n(pounds)") +
  scale_color_discrete(labels = c('Female','Male')) +
  ggtitle('Legend with Multiple Variables')
